\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13-24. R. montanus }group. Glabrous or pubescent perennials 5-50 cm. Rhizome often with fibres and sometimes with hairs. Basal leaves 3- to 5(-7)-lobed; segments obovate, dentate; cauline leaves deeply 3- to 5-lobed with narrower, usually entire segments. Flowers 1-3(-5), 20-40 mm in diameter. Achenes 2·5-3·5 mm, compressed, sharply keeled; beak 0·5-2·5 mm, hooked.
\par 

